            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cook the base",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Melt {{unsalted-butter}} of butter in a large saucepan over a medium-low heat. Add the {{onion}} onion and cook for 6 minutes until soft. Add the {{garlic}} of garlic and {{cumin-ground}} of cumin and cook for 1 minute.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{carrot}} of chopped carrots and {{parsnip}} of chopped parsnips. Pour in {{stock-vegetable}} of hot stock. Bring to a simmer and cook for 22 to 25 minutes until both vegetables are very tender.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Blend and finish",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Blend until smooth. Stir in {{double-cream}} of cream and the juice of {{lemon}} lemon. Taste and season with salt.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle into bowls. Add a swirl of cream to each bowl.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "The lemon juice is essential here ,  add it fully and taste. Add more if still too sweet. A slightly larger pinch of cumin also cuts through the sweetness.",
                "cause": "Both carrots and parsnips are sweet vegetables; together they are very sweet.",
                "symptom": "Soup is too sweet"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Remove the central fibrous core from larger parsnips before cooking. Blend for at least 60 seconds. Pass through a sieve for a very smooth result.",
                "cause": "Large parsnips have a woody core that does not blend smoothly.",
                "symptom": "Texture has fibrous strands"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add extra hot stock or water after blending until the consistency is right. A thick soup is fine; one that moves like porridge is too far.",
                "cause": "Parsnips are starchy and thicken considerably when blended.",
                "symptom": "Soup is very thick"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Three-quarters of a teaspoon is the upper limit for this quantity of vegetables. If too strong, a small extra knob of butter stirred in softens it.",
                "cause": "Too much cumin for the volume of vegetables.",
                "symptom": "Cumin is the dominant flavour"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Carrot and parsnip soup is a British winter standard. Both vegetables are among the cheapest available from autumn through March. Their sweetness means the soup needs very little added flavour to work. It is the kind of soup that uses up the root vegetables that pile up in most winter kitchens.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
